# 🧑‍💻 SunnyBest Forecasting System (SFS) – Role Alignment

This section defines how different technical roles interact with the SFS, ensuring clear ownership, collaboration, and production readiness.

The system is designed so that **Data Engineers, Data Scientists, Machine Learning Engineers, and AI Engineers** can contribute independently while working within a unified architecture.

---

# 🏗️ 1. Data Engineer

## Responsibility
Owns the **data foundation** of the system, ensuring that all datasets are reliable, structured, and production-ready.

## Core Focus Areas
- Data ingestion (CSV, APIs, databases)
- Data cleaning and validation
- Data modelling (fact/dimension tables)
- Pipeline orchestration
- Feature-ready dataset creation

## SFS Components
- `src/data/make_dataset.py`
- `src/data/validation.py`
- `src/features/build_features.py`
- `src/features/calendar_features.py`
- `src/features/demand_features.py`
- Raw → processed data layers (`data/raw/`, `data/processed/`)

## Key Contributions
- Builds reusable pipelines for:
  - sales data
  - inventory data
  - promotions
  - external drivers (weather, calendar)
- Ensures data consistency across modules
- Provides clean inputs for modelling and AI layers

## Outputs
- Validated datasets
- Feature tables for modelling
- Structured data for API and dashboard use

---

# 📊 2. Data Scientist

## Responsibility
Owns **analytical modelling and business insight generation**, translating data into meaningful predictions and decisions.

## Core Focus Areas
- Forecasting models
- Statistical analysis
- Causal inference (promotion impact)
- Experimentation and validation
- Scenario analysis

## SFS Components
- `src/forecasting/`
- `src/pricing/`
- `src/inventory/stockout_model.py`
- `src/planning/scenario_engine.py`
- Segmentation workflows

## Key Contributions
- Develops demand forecasting models
- Builds price elasticity and promotion uplift models
- Designs stockout prediction logic
- Performs backtesting and evaluation
- Interprets results for business use

## Outputs
- Trained models
- Forecast outputs
- Analytical insights
- Inputs to decision and planning modules

---

# ⚙️ 3. Machine Learning Engineer

## Responsibility
Owns **model productionisation and system reliability**, ensuring models run efficiently and reliably in real-world environments.

## Core Focus Areas
- Model deployment
- API integration
- Pipeline automation
- Monitoring and alerting
- Performance optimisation

## SFS Components
- `src/api/app.py`
- `src/api/routes/predict.py`
- `src/forecasting/pipelines.py`
- `src/forecasting/backtest.py`
- `src/monitoring/`

## Key Contributions
- Deploys forecasting and inventory models via API
- Builds scalable prediction pipelines
- Automates model training and retraining
- Implements monitoring (accuracy, drift, alerts)
- Ensures system performance and reliability

## Outputs
- Production-ready APIs
- Automated pipelines
- Monitoring dashboards and logs
- Scalable model infrastructure

---

# 🤖 4. AI Engineer

## Responsibility
Owns the **intelligent layer of the system**, enabling natural language interaction, reasoning, and decision support.

## Core Focus Areas
- GenAI integration (LLMs)
- Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG)
- Prompt engineering
- Agent design
- Explainability and decision support

## SFS Components
- `src/ai/copilot.py`
- `src/ai/services/assistant.py`
- `src/ai/rag/`
- `src/api/routes/ai.py`

## Key Contributions
- Builds AI assistant for business users
- Enables natural language queries on forecasts and KPIs
- Generates explanations for model outputs
- Supports decision reasoning (why/what-if analysis)
- Integrates knowledge base (`docs/`) into AI responses

## Outputs
- AI assistant responses
- Insight summaries
- Decision explanations
- Conversational interface for the system

